citations:
    citation-asos-daenerys-iii:
        source: source-asos
        properties:
            locator: "Daenerys III"
            text_from_source: "There is a reason. A dragon is no slave. And Dany swept the lash down as hard as she could across the slaver's face... 'Drogon,' she sang out loudly, sweetly, all her fear forgotten. 'Dracarys.'"
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "The sack of Astapor. Daenerys trades all her ships and goods (plus the dragon Drogon) to Kraznys for the Unsullied. She reveals she speaks Valyrian, strikes Kraznys with the harpy's fingers whip, and commands Drogon to burn him. The Unsullied kill the Good Masters on Daenerys's command. She frees all the Unsullied and invites them to choose to serve her. Grey Worm is named their commander."
